# GreatWall Signature Scheme

This repository provides reference and optimized implementations of **GreatWall**, a post-quantum signature scheme.

## Environment

All code was tested on the following platform:

- **Operating System:** Ubuntu 22.04.5 LTS  
- **Compiler:** GCC 11.4.0  

The optimized implementation requires support for **AVX2** instructions.

## Related Implementations

For comparison and benchmarking purposes, we refer to the following implementations:

- AIMer: https://aimer-signature.org/  
- BN++Rain: https://github.com/isec-tugraz/bnpp_helium_signatures/tree/main/bnpp_rain  


## Build and Test

'''
cd Reference_Implementation
python3 make_clean.py
python3 test_and_bench.py


cd Optimized_Implementation 
python3 make_clean.py 
python3 test_and_bench.py 
'''

## Repository Structure


├──────── Reference_Implementation/
│   ├── greatwall128_N16/
│   ├── greatwall128_N64/
│   ├── greatwall128_N256/
│   ├── greatwall128_N2048/
│   ├── greatwall192_N16/
│   ├── greatwall192_N64/
│   ├── greatwall192_N256/
│   ├── greatwall256_N16/
│   ├── greatwall256_N64/
│   └── greatwall256_N256/
│
└──────── Optimized_Implementation/
    ├── greatwall128_N16/
    ├── greatwall128_N64/
    ├── greatwall128_N256/
    ├── greatwall128_N2048/
    ├── greatwall192_N16/
    ├── greatwall192_N64/
    ├── greatwall192_N256/
    ├── greatwall256_N16/
    ├── greatwall256_N64/
    └── greatwall256_N256/


- `greatwall{128,192,256}` denote the target security levels.
- `N ∈ {16, 64, 256, 2048}` denotes the number of parties.
- `Reference_Implementation` provides a portable reference implementation.
- `Optimized_Implementation` provides an AVX2-optimized implementation.

